node.title: 'Heroic' police officer saves two boys from almost certain death in flooded NSW river
node.description: A NSW police officer will be recommended for a bravery award after he jumped into the flooded Lachlan River to rescue two boys clinging desperately to a log in the fast-moving current.

node.title: NT records no new cases of COVID-19 overnight following nine Binjari cases
node.description: The Chief Minister says the Northern Territory has recorded no new cases of coronavirus overnight after nine new cases were detected in the remote community of Binjari on Saturday evening.
